The President of the United States congratulates the people of Sri Lanka on the successful and peaceful conclusion of their presidential election. He also commends the outgoing administration for facilitating a smooth transition of power. The election is seen as a symbol of hope for democracy supporters worldwide. International and domestic monitors were allowed to do their job, and the Sri Lankan people cast their ballots peacefully. The United States looks forward to strengthening its partnership with Sri Lanka and working with President Sirisena to promote peace, democracy, and prosperity for all Sri Lankans.